cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and proposes a clustering algorithm for energy efficient data transmission. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed algorithm is based on Whale Optimization Algorithm (WOA), which is a metaheuristic optimization algorithm inspired by the hunting behavior of humpback whales. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed algorithm involves selecting cluster heads based on a fitness function, which can be seen as a form of machine learning. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with designing a system (i.e., a wireless sensor network) and optimizing its performance through the proposed algorithm. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for cluster head selection in wireless sensor networks, which can be seen as a data structure and algorithm problem.
